rComments: Excellent Prof and person.  He did a great job serving all the students at UTSC for decades! Thanks Mike!! S.

He's a really nice professor and all. The assignments were vague, and I think it just depends on which TA you have in order to get a good mark. But the exam really screwed me over; you really need to know every specific point he has in your lecture notes to get full marks.

Bunce is a great prof. he explains concepts and themes very clearly. he made me the course materials interesting and easy to understand. He is one of the best prof. i had in utsc. i wish he wasnt retired...

he was one of the nicest prof at utsc. its important to go to class as he doesnt post up notes like others. final exam was fair. overall, hes a good prof.

Prof. Bunce has a hard time controlling the class and has a complete aversion to letting us out on time.  The lectures were interesting, but useless: everything discussed in class was posted online.  It seems to me that he is on the verge of retiring and is losing interest in teaching.
